A security guard who was beaten up by a crowd at Moses Mabhida stadium during the Kaiser Chiefs and Free State stars game is recovering well. Kaiser Chiefs announced on it's Twitter account that Kaiser Chiefs Marketing Director Jessica Motaung visited Sabelo Masiza. "We are so glad that the security marshal, Sabelo Maziba is recovering well after he was beaten up on Saturday at the stadium and left unconscious." Jessica visited him on Tuesday in Durban to check up on him. The club wished him a speedy recovery. 